metadata.name: Breakfast #127
metadata.description:
Breakfast is a real-time generative system for creating complex arrangements of primitive forms. Inspired by suprematism, its aim is to arrange simple and boldly coloured shapes in pleasing ways. Driven by a real-time physics engine, it allows for direct collaboration between artist, audience, and generative system. 

Original artwork by Kelly Milligan (kellymilligan.art) in Titirangi, Auckland, New Zealand - Published November 2021 on fxhash.xyz

Upon sale of final token:
- 20% of proceeds will be donated to Forest & Bird (https://www.forestandbird.org.nz/) for conservation efforts within Aotearoa (New Zealand)
- 5% of proceeds will be sent to @liabru (brm.io) for his work on Matter.js

Controls:
- Save: CMD/CTRL + S - Save as a 4096x4096 still image
- Churn*: C or OPTION/ALT + C to toggle churning and direction
- Gravity*: G to toggle gravity
- Bounce*: B to toggle bounciness
* Exclusive to tokens containing the feature

Notes: 
- Churners move for 15s each minute as an abstract clock, disabled by controls

metadata.name: tur1ng #239
metadata.description:
‘tur1ng’ consists of audible image architectures based on the principle of Turing machines. These systems are mathematical models of computation that manipulate symbols on a strip of tape according to a table of rules. The machine first writes a symbol in a cell on the tape, then either moves the tape one cell left or right, then, based on the observed symbol and the machine's own state in the table, either proceeds to another instruction or halts computation.

In ‘tur1ng’, rules are stored as colors and the original tape cells are constructed from a two dimensional array. The sound unfolds as the algorithm proceeds: monitoring these binary songs requires being attentive to changes in the state or behavior of the system over time so that appropriate interventions or other process-related activities may be carried out. Another feature of listening algorithms is that it often has to be done as a background or secondary task or, perhaps, in parallel with one or more other primary tasks.

Touch to listen.

metadata.name: Annihilate This Week #135
metadata.description:
This is a companion piece to "Saturday Night's Alright (For Fighting)" (project #14045). Same algorithm of the previous one, only slightly modified, the main difference is that here the daily variations are all mixed up together and the output doesn't change based on the current day.

This is intended to be a gift for all collectors and the community of fx(hash) that showed so much support for the "Saturday" project, really beyond my expectations.

50% of the royalties goes to the minter, do with the piece whatever you'd like, hold it, sell or trade it, or even burn it if you really don't like it :)

Thank you!

----

Made with p5.js
